      "content": "To: Compliance Team\n\nAs we continue to refine our client onboarding process, it is essential that we adhere to the stringent requirements of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). In light of this, we will be implementing new protocols to ensure our handling of client data is compliant with the regulation.\n\nWhen taking on a new client, our onboarding team will conduct a Data Protection Impact Assessment (DPIA) to identify the Processing Activities that will be performed on their personal data. This assessment will inform our subsequent steps, including the designation of a Data Controller and Data Processor, as required by the regulation. Our Data Controller will be responsible for ensuring that the client's personal data is processed in accordance with the principles of lawfulness, fairness, and transparency, including obtaining explicit Consent from the client where necessary.\n\nTo minimize the scope of our Processing Activities, we will implement Data Minimization and Storage Limitation measures, ensuring that we only process the data necessary to fulfill our obligations to the client. We will also maintain accurate records of our Processing Activities, including the Data Protection Impact Assessment, to demonstrate our accountability and compliance with the regulation.\n\nIn the event of a Breach Notification, we will notify the client and the relevant Supervisory Authority, as required",
